        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Intermediate Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Pyromania</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='84' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/magination/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(4.2)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=20632">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=8891">Simon "dReshHyren" Pang</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=8891&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I have been playing this deck for quite a while and with the addition of Dream&#39;s End, it has only gotten better. It&#39;s relatively easy to play, as long as you are able to be patient, althought it requires quite a few rare cards.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> January 14, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> **MAGI** <br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(376)">Barak</a> :: (<a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>), <a href="javascript:card_browser(369)">Lava <a href="javascript:card_browser(395)">Balamant</a></a> <br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(543)">Raega</a> :: <a href="javascript:card_browser(536)">Braggle</a>, Fireball, <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a> <br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(676)">Amanax</a> :: <a href="javascript:card_browser(392)">Syphon Vortex</a> <br />
<br />
**CREATURES** (20) <br />
1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a> <br />
1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(369)">Lava <a href="javascript:card_browser(395)">Balamant</a></a> <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(370)">Magma Hyren</a> <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(537)">Er<a href="javascript:card_browser(377)">Gar</a></a> <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(536)">Braggle</a> <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(583)">Core Grag</a> <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(671)">Diomant</a> <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(672}<a href="javascript:card_browser({516)">Gia</a>nt <a href="javascript:card_browser(394)">Arboll</a></a> <br />
<br />
**RELICS** (11) <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(386)">Scroll of Fire</a> <br />
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(507)">Relic Stalker</a> <br />
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(512)">Warrior&#39;s Boots</a> <br />
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(678)">Abraxin&#39;s Crown</a> <br />
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(787)">Rayje&#39;s Sword</a> <br />
<br />
**SPELLS** (11) <br />
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(355)">Shockwave</a> <br />
1 Fireball <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(392)">Syphon Vortex</a> <br />
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(498)">Thunderquake</a> <br />
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(680)">Lava Flow</a>   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> 1st Magi: Barak <br />
Barak is a wonderful setup Magi. He gets you the cards you need, when you need them. You always want to go first with Barak, because his starting energy is huge. In most cases, I would just grab the Lava Balamant, but if you know that your opponent runs Corrupts and the like in their deck, go for the Arbolit too. Also, the Arbolit is great defense against the Dark Twins/Corrupt setup. Trying to hold out with Barak is key to getting the cards you need. <br />
When you Prophecy, you will want to go for the Braggles first, so that Barak can stay alive. If your opponent is playing a huge Creature deck, grab the Shockwave. If they&#39;re playing a swarm type deck, grab the Core Grag. <br />
<br />
2nd Magi: Raega <br />
Extremely explosive Magi. Starting with a Braggle and Fireball, she is insane. Plus, her power is amazing. There&#39;s really not much to stop her from Cremating whatever you want, then playing the Braggle. Basically, she sits there and beats on the opposing Magi. Not too hard to understand. <br />
<br />
3rd Magi - Amanax <br />
Amanax is a great finisher. Starting with a Syphon Vortex, he is deadly with an Abraxin&#39;s Crown. When you reveal him, you&#39;ll want to target the largest Creature possible with the Syphon Vortex so that he gets the most benefit from his Effect. Syphon Vortexing a Magi doesn&#39;t give Amanax energy, but it does surprise the opponent! <br />
<br />
**CREATURES** <br />
Arbolit - Dark Twins grabs Corrupt? Give them an Arbolit. Simply a tech. Also starting for Barak and Raega. <br />
<br />
Lava Balamant - Starting for Barak. <br />
<br />
Magma Hyren - Pretty darn versatile card. Great for giving Braggles energy so that they can take out a Creature, or simply for their Fireballs. <br />
<br />
Ergar - The Heart of the deck. Ergars + Giant Arbolls makes me happy. Combine with Scroll of Fire to deal super damage. <br />
<br />
Braggle - Great attacking and defending card. <br />
<br />
Core Grag - Weenie wipeout. Yes, you have to pay a regional penalty, but if it&#39;s not going to be worth it, don&#39;t play it. <br />
<br />
Diomant - The great fire squadron. Play these with an Ergar or two, Spark away then Energy Transfer all but one energy to your Magi. Combine with Abraxin&#39;s Crown for an amazing 4 for 1! <br />
<br />
Giant Arboll - Wonderful with Ergars. Play these, Spark your enemies to doom, then return energy to your Magi so that you can play some spell to finish them off! <br />
<br />
**RELICS** <br />
Scroll of Fire - It really is a pity that these only affect Creatures. In any case, they work wonders with Ergars and Core Grags. <br />
<br />
Relic Stalker - Need I say more? <br />
<br />
Warrior&#39;s Boots - Works best with Braggle. Otherwise, another duh. <br />
<br />
Abraxin&#39;s Crown - Wonderful surprise when you play this with a Syphon Vortex. <br />
<br />
Rayje&#39;s Sword - Tech vs. those evil Burrow decks and Zannah <br />
<br />
**SPELLS** <br />
Shockwave - That Pylofuf bothering you? Just Shockwave away! <br />
<br />
Fireball - Starting for Raega. Also a very versatile card. <br />
<br />
Syphon Vortex - The Second Heart of the deck. Great for hitting... anything (see Abraxin&#39;s Crown)! <br />
<br />
Thunderquake - Another weenie wipeout. <br />
<br />
Lava Flow - Amazing card. Zannah giving you trouble? Just play this first and she can&#39;t do a single thing about it.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=20632"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=20632" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
